 Note on the Trash Flag (-t)
 The --trash flag takes an optional argument.

    Default: sysmain -t (Cleans standard ~/.local/share/Trash)

    Custom: sysmain -t/tmp/junk or sysmain --trash=/tmp/junk

    WARNING: Do not use a space (sysmain -t /tmp). 
    Standard POSIX getopt ignores optional arguments if there is a space, 
    so it will clean the default trash and ignore your path.
